public interface DimensionsObjectCollection

The root interface in the Dimensions collection hierarchy. A collection contains a group of uniquely identifiable Dimensions objects of a certain type.

refresh

void refresh()
             throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Updates the objects in the collection to reflect the current base database data. After calling refresh() you should explicitly reacquire all previously obtained references to this collection's objects and their dependent objects and/or collections in order to ensure consistency of operations.

Note: Changes to the data held in the Dimensions base database made by other processes (e.g. AdminConsole or other DMPMCLI sessions) after the collection was accessed for the first time might not be automatically reflected in the collection unless the refresh method is explicitly invoked.

Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs
